description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brief Description of the Role: &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated and enthusiastic individual to work predominantly with the joinery team on a part time basis in the estates maintenance section to carry out a range of maintenance duties across the Foundation Trust premises, including joinery, building fabric repairs, painting/decorating, undertake basic diagnostics and repair of faults in mechanical and installations; plant and equipment, grounds and gardens maintenance and general support across all core engineering trades.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job holder will be expected to carry out routine maintenance requests in an efficient and effective manner to support successful delivery of a customer focussed estate maintenance service for the foundation trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Summary of most important Experience/Skills/Qualifications required:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant relevant experience with a background in the maintenance industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of carrying out general building maintenance, problem solving, making safe equipment and carrying out repairs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal Enquiries to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paul Noble, Estate Manager, Estates Department, Bradford Royal Infirmary, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01274 364684.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer staff gymnasiums on both hospital sites, excellent pension scheme and advice on childcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 18.11.20 (This date may change dependent on the response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
